article.description: Nash leads North Dakota past Mayfield St. 76-39
article.headline: Nash leads North Dakota past Mayfield St. 76-39
article.linkText: Nash leads North Dakota past Mayfield St. 76-39
article.story: GRAND FORKS, N.D. -- Jaron Nash had his first career double-double with 16 points and 12 rebounds to lead North Dakota to a dominating 76-39 win over NAIA's Mayville State on Tuesday night. Josiah Coleman, who was 3 of 5 from outside the arc, had 13 points and Quinton Hooker added 11. Mayville State led 14-13 midway of the first half, but North Dakota(1-1) went on a 10-0 run and built a 38-24 halftime lead. The Comets were limited to just 15 points in the second half. They committed 27 turnovers in the game. UND made 7 of 18 3-pointers, and hit 26 of 55 field goal attempts. The Comets made 14 of 46 shots from the field. Chuck Robinson led Mayville State with 14 points and 10 rebounds. Michael Lindsey contributed 11 points.
